Caterpillar: Who are YOU?
Alice: I-I hardly know, sir, I must have changed several times since I got up this morning.
Caterpillar: Explain yourself!
Alice: I’m afraid I can’t explain myself, for I hardly know myself.
Caterpillar: WHO ARE YOU?
Alice: I do not precisely know, I know I’d like to be more than three inches tall!
Caterpillar: I am three inches tall exactly, there is nothing wrong with being three inches tall!
=> END